HEADWORD: Productivity
<hw>Pro`duc*tiv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
or state of being productive; productiveness.</def>
<rj><au>Emerson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not indeed as the product, but as the producing power, the
<qex>productivity</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Productress</ent>⟦br⟧
